# MCP Module

The MCP module seeds a lightweight automation registry that mirrors the
`FastMCP` tooling expectations.

## Enabling the Module

Render with `mcp_module=enabled` to scaffold `shared/mcp/tooling.py`. The helper registers sample tools
and falls back gracefully if `fastmcp` is unavailable.

## Smoke Check

```bash
uv run python -c "from shared.mcp import tooling; print(tooling.list_tools())"
```

Extend the registry by adding new `@registry.register(...)` functions inside `tooling.py`.
